[normal]3 [bold]Motor insurance - a broken market[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]As car insurance is a legal requirement for motorists, it is vital the provision of this product functions in a way that is competitive and treats consumers 
[normal]fairly both in terms of value and their ability to make genuine claims. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]I
[normal]n our view, motorists are ill-served by a market dominated by a handful of providers who 
[normal]have an agenda 
[normal]to 
[normal]persuade politicians and 
[normal]government 
[normal]of the need to introduce further legal
[normal] reforms 
[normal]that will serve 
[normal]to boost 
[normal]their already substantial profits. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Five key facts underpin our analy
[normal]sis of the broken state of this
[normal] market, from a consumer’s point of view:  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We will look at each of these points in turn and substantiate them.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.1[bold] [bold]Market domination[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The Association of British Insurers says
[normal] there are 23.8 private vehicles insured in the 
[normal]UK
[normal]. Published financial information show
[normal]s
